25/01/2009
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- The trial of retired Serbian General Vlastimir Djordjevic, accused of war crimes against ethnic Albanians in Kosovo in 1999, is scheduled to start on Tuesday (January 27th), media are reporting. In 1999, Djordjevic was Serbia's deputy interior minister and head of the State Security Agency. He is accused of complicity in the murder, persecution, deportation and forced displacement of Albanian civilians. In one incident, 44 members of an ethnic Albanian family were killed in March 1999 by Serb forces, including some under Djordjevic's command. (B92, RTS - 23/01/09)
